{title: A Distant Land To Roam}
{artist: Ralph Stanley}
{composer: Written by A.P. Carter}

[C]I remember very well
On one dark and dreary day
Just as I was leaving home
For a [G7]distant land to [C]roam
Mother said (mother said)
My dear boy (my dear boy)
I hope to see you next year [G7]again
Fare thee [C]well (fare thee well)
Fare thee well (fare thee well)

So I left my dear old home
For a [G7]distant land to [C]roam
Now I wandered far away
From my home I’ve gone astray
Now I’m coming coming home
Never [G7]more from thee to [C]roam
Repeat #2
And these words she said to me
As she took me by the hand
If on earth we meet no more
May we [G7]meet at God’s right [C]hand
Repeat #2